// @test regression/INV055-void-assignment
// @description Assigning the result of a void-returning builtin to a variable is TV's CE10098 "Void expression cannot be assigned to a variable" (probed array.push / matrix.reverse, 2026-06-10). We inferred void calls as "unknown" (assignable to anything) and missed it for all 127 void builtins. Found by building coverage for the fixture-coverage census's uncovered matrix.* block. A bare void call as its own statement stays legal, and a non-void initializer is unaffected. See investigations/INV055-void-assignment/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=4, column=1, message="Void expression cannot be assigned to a variable"
// @expects error: line=6, column=1, message="Void expression cannot be assigned to a variable"
//@version=6
indicator("t")
a = array.new<float>(0)
bad1 = array.push(a, 1.0)
m = matrix.new<float>(2, 2, 0.0)
bad2 = matrix.reverse(m)
array.push(a, 2.0)
ok = array.size(a)
plot(close + ok)
